page.title: 07HOUSES NEW AND OLD
page.content: The next oldest house we saw was an early twentieth century semi_detached with pebble dash on the wall, and a slate roof.We also saw some semi_detached council houses which were built in the 1950s.They were built in brick with red tiled roofs. We saw some large semi_detached private housing.They were built with red bricks and red tiled roofs.They have large bay windows and they were built in the mid twentieth century. There are alot of bunglows in Rowlands Gill. Rowlands Gill is in the South_East of our block. There was alot of modern semi_detached houses in Fellside Park. They have all been built in the past five years.They are still building on this estate.
